WEBVTT

00:01.702 --> 00:04.172
[ Earl Narrating ]
Me and Randy love watchin'
old war movies,

00:04.238 --> 00:06.240
but sometimes
they'll trick you.

00:06.307 --> 00:08.609
You think it'll be cool,
with gunfights and explosions,

00:08.676 --> 00:10.844
but then you end up
just gettin' uncomfortable.

00:10.911 --> 00:14.482
Oh, my God, Johnny.
They shot ya.

00:14.548 --> 00:17.218
Ricky, tell Mom
I said good-bye.

00:17.285 --> 00:19.019
You can't die, Johnny.
You're my only brother.

00:19.087 --> 00:21.155
[ Johnny ]
I'm sorry.

00:21.222 --> 00:24.825
I just wanna tell you one thing
before I go, Ricky.

00:24.892 --> 00:27.128
I love you.

00:27.195 --> 00:30.231
[ Earl Narrating ]
See, Randy and I are as close
as two brothers can be.

00:30.298 --> 00:33.667
We've just never actually
said "I love you."

00:33.734 --> 00:38.072
I know it's hard to hear,
and Lord knows it's hard to say,

00:38.139 --> 00:41.542
but sometimes brothers
need to tell each other
those simple words.

00:41.609 --> 00:43.444
I love you.

00:43.511 --> 00:46.947
[ Ricky ] God, Johnny. Why do
brothers wait till the end of
their lives to say these things?

00:47.014 --> 00:49.049
I love ya too, Johnny.

01:00.694 --> 01:04.232
I'm gonna go drop a deuce.
I'm gonna go squish bugs.

01:04.298 --> 01:06.800
My name is Earl.

01:10.804 --> 01:12.706
[ Both Laughing ]

01:16.110 --> 01:18.779
Do you ever tell your brothers
or sisters that you love 'em?

01:18.846 --> 01:23.317
There's one I would say it to,
two who would say it to me,
but I would not say it back,

01:23.384 --> 01:25.319
one who would interpret it
sexually...

01:25.386 --> 01:27.288
and three I cannot
locate since the flood.

01:27.355 --> 01:31.492
Hey, mo. I need to use
your car to go to Henderson.
Subaru's got ants in it again.

01:31.559 --> 01:33.527
You just need to find
where the queen lives.

01:33.594 --> 01:35.596
Queen lives on a Blow Pop
under the driver's seat.

01:35.663 --> 01:37.698
Every time I reach for it,
her soldiers attack me.

01:37.765 --> 01:40.568
It's just a Blow Pop.
They'll be done in a few days.

01:40.634 --> 01:42.536
- They got, like,
a million tongues.
- Can't wait.

01:42.603 --> 01:44.738
Stupid deaf lawyer's got me
drivin' all over state...

01:44.805 --> 01:47.275
gettin' people to drop
the various restrainin' orders
they got against me.

01:47.341 --> 01:49.843
- Says it'll help me in court.
- Who's in Henderson?

01:49.910 --> 01:52.346
The girl in the wheelchair
that you pushed down the hill?

01:52.413 --> 01:54.248
No, that little line-cutter
lives in Nathanville.

01:54.315 --> 01:57.285
Remember that cranky bat
with the hearin' aid that
used to manage the trailer park?

01:57.351 --> 01:59.620
[ Earl Narrating ]
Joy was speakin'
of Millie Banks.

01:59.687 --> 02:01.655
Citation.

02:01.722 --> 02:06.160
No La-Z-Boys on the lawn
unless they match the color
of the mobile home.

02:06.227 --> 02:10.398
Twenty dollars?
Yep. There goes your
book money for the decade.

02:11.799 --> 02:13.534
Citation.

02:13.601 --> 02:15.669
Christmas-light reindeer
still on the lawn.

02:15.736 --> 02:17.638
It's April.

02:17.705 --> 02:20.241
What are you talkin' about?
That-- That's an Easter pig.

02:20.308 --> 02:22.943
Don't blaspheme
the resurrection, jerk.

02:23.010 --> 02:25.346
You got a citation
for that too?

02:25.413 --> 02:28.682
Oh, you'll get
your citation... in hell.

02:30.884 --> 02:34.955
** [ Heavy Metal On Stereo ]
Citation. No speakers
in your window on weekdays.

02:35.022 --> 02:39.059
You can't even half-hear
outta that stupid hearin' aid
in your ear anyway.

02:39.126 --> 02:41.662
- I can feel the bass notes.
- You can feel the bass notes.

02:41.729 --> 02:44.432
- I got a bass note for ya.
- You know what?
This is America.

02:44.498 --> 02:47.935
I think you like
the bass notes.
[ Voices Become Muffled ]

02:49.370 --> 02:53.073
[ Both Muffled, Indistinct ]

02:53.140 --> 02:56.444
[ Both Continue, Muffled ]

02:56.510 --> 02:59.480
I hate her! I hate her
like the Taliban hate freedom!
** [ Heavy Metal On Radio ]

02:59.547 --> 03:03.150
And how are we supposed to
listen to heavy metal
on a wimpy little tape player?

03:03.217 --> 03:05.553
- [ Randy ]
It's craziness.
- Today we can't have bass.

03:05.619 --> 03:08.356
Tomorrow my illegal fireworks
won't even be legal.

03:08.422 --> 03:10.891
** [ Switches Off ]
We gotta fight back.

03:12.426 --> 03:14.395
[ Earl Narrating ]
The plan was to lure Millie...

03:14.462 --> 03:17.665
away from her preacher shows
long enough to go steal stuff.

03:17.731 --> 03:20.601
But you had to be extra sneaky
about stealin' from Millie.

03:20.668 --> 03:24.104
Back off my birdseed,
you tree rat!

03:24.171 --> 03:26.073
[ Earl Narrating ]
Millie was packin' heat.

03:26.139 --> 03:27.941
[ Squirrel Chittering ]
[ Laughing ]

03:29.109 --> 03:31.144
You guys ready to do this?

03:31.211 --> 03:33.581
Breaker 1-9,
this here's the Rubber Duck.

03:33.647 --> 03:36.049
You got a copy on me,
Pigpen? Come on.

03:36.116 --> 03:38.452
Nice. "Convoy."
They should make more
movies out of country songs.

03:41.355 --> 03:43.291
* We got a great big convoy *

03:43.357 --> 03:45.225
* Rockin' through the night *

03:45.293 --> 03:48.296
* Yeah, we got
a great big convoy
Ain't she a beautiful sight *

03:48.362 --> 03:51.999
* Come on and join our convoy
Ain't nothin' gonna
get in our way *

03:52.065 --> 03:56.904
* We gonna roll this truckin'
convoy cross the U.S.A. *

03:56.970 --> 03:58.872
* Convoy *

04:00.374 --> 04:02.443
* Convoy **

04:02.510 --> 04:04.912
10-4, Rubber Duck.
Pigpen's got his ears on.

04:04.978 --> 04:09.082
- You have to push
the button down.
- Can you hear me?

04:09.149 --> 04:11.852
Hello?
Yes, I can hear you.

04:13.387 --> 04:15.723
Who is that?

04:15.789 --> 04:18.426
Is her hearin' aid pickin' up
my walkie-talkie?

04:18.492 --> 04:20.461
[ Earl ]
Hello?

04:20.528 --> 04:23.331
Is that you, Lord?

04:24.432 --> 04:27.901
Oh, snap. Go on.
Talk to her. Be God.

04:27.968 --> 04:30.638
[ Clears Throat ]

04:30.704 --> 04:33.307
- Yes, it is I, God.
- [ Chuckles ]

04:33.374 --> 04:35.509
I was in
the "neighborhoodeth,"

04:35.576 --> 04:39.447
and I wanted to test
thou's faith.

04:39.513 --> 04:43.016
I am yours.
Test me as you will.

04:44.752 --> 04:48.622
- "Putteth" thy left foot in.
- [ Chuckling ]

04:51.692 --> 04:54.628
"Putteth" thy left foot out.

04:57.765 --> 05:01.502
"Putteth" thy left foot in...

05:01.569 --> 05:04.237
and "shaketh" it all about.

05:04.304 --> 05:06.674
[ All Chuckling ]

05:06.740 --> 05:09.610
[ Earl Narrating ]
After the Hokey Pokey,
some toe-touches...

05:09.677 --> 05:11.645
and a badly failed
cartwheel,

05:11.712 --> 05:14.247
we put our powers
to more practical use.

05:14.314 --> 05:19.853
Now "rippeth" up
all thy Mobile Home Owners
Association citations...

05:21.154 --> 05:25.192
and "baketh" yummy dessert items
for thy neighbors.

05:25.258 --> 05:27.060
[ Earl Narrating ]
It was fun bein' God,

05:27.127 --> 05:29.997
but we found that great power
came with great responsibility,

05:30.063 --> 05:32.132
includin' making sure
the yummy desserts were yummy.

05:32.199 --> 05:34.468
Do not "maketh" carrot cake.

05:34.535 --> 05:38.171
The Lord hates carrot cake.
It is the devil's food.

05:38.238 --> 05:41.174
But that doesn't mean
don't make devil's food cake.

05:41.241 --> 05:43.343
I love that stuff.

05:45.379 --> 05:47.948
[ Earl Narrating ]
On the sixth day,
we went for the gold.

05:48.015 --> 05:50.183
[ Earl On Walkie-talkie ]
That's right, your gold.

05:50.250 --> 05:53.253
And your silver.
Anything pawnable.

05:53.320 --> 05:56.690
Give it to the pawn lady
across the way
with the nice rear end.

05:58.291 --> 06:01.429
I'm a man.
I notice things.

06:01.495 --> 06:04.998
[ Earl Narrating ]
That was our last commandment.
We had bled Millie dry.

06:06.233 --> 06:09.269
I don't know why he asked me
to give you this stuff.

06:09.336 --> 06:13.040
He's mysterious.
He also makes hurricanes
and gave nipples to men.

06:13.106 --> 06:15.709
The important thing is,
you do what he tells you to.

06:16.744 --> 06:18.746
Are you wearin' earrings?

06:20.881 --> 06:23.383
[ Earl Narrating ]
And from the seventh day on,
we rested.

06:23.451 --> 06:26.119
I'll get that signed for you.
I should probably
go see Millie anyway.

06:26.186 --> 06:29.189
She's on my list--
made a lady think I was God.

06:29.256 --> 06:31.492
Thanks, Earl.

06:31.559 --> 06:35.563
When I was a child, there was
a man who lived in a box by
the dump who told me he was God.

06:35.629 --> 06:38.632
How old were you
when you realized he was
just a crazy old homeless guy?

06:38.699 --> 06:40.934
Please don't talk about God
that way.

06:43.303 --> 06:46.206
Hey, Darnell, you ever tell
your sister you love her?

06:46.273 --> 06:49.877
Once when I thought
she was dead, but she was just
passed out from low blood sugar.

06:49.943 --> 06:52.513
I'm still glad I said it.
Now they have her on insulin.

06:52.580 --> 06:55.015
Who knows when I'll get
another chance?

06:56.517 --> 06:58.285
[ Earl Narrating ]
We got to Henderson late...

06:58.351 --> 07:00.821
'cause Randy
turned the directions
into a paper airplane...

07:00.888 --> 07:03.290
to see if it would lift the car
off the ground.

07:03.356 --> 07:06.126
It didn't,
and we lost the directions.

07:06.193 --> 07:08.662
I brought Millie replacements
for the things we stole.

07:08.729 --> 07:11.298
I was hopin' she'd see
all that "voice of God" stuff...

07:11.364 --> 07:14.167
as, well,
a harmless prank.

07:14.234 --> 07:16.069
What is this place?
A convent?

07:16.136 --> 07:18.271
* We got a great big convent
truckin' through-- *

07:18.338 --> 07:20.874
Nuns. Nuns. Nuns.

07:20.941 --> 07:24.578
Excuse me.
Uh, do you know
a Millie Banks?

07:24.645 --> 07:27.615
Sister Millie?
Yes, she's inside.

07:29.583 --> 07:31.619
Sister Millie?

07:31.685 --> 07:34.321
I bet nuns are awesome
basketball players,

07:34.387 --> 07:36.890
especially the ones
who can fly.

07:36.957 --> 07:39.226
[ Earl Narrating ]
In addition to thinkin'
nuns could fly,

07:39.292 --> 07:42.530
Randy also thought
they were pretty,
but knew that that was wrong,

07:42.596 --> 07:44.632
and tried hard
not to focus on it.

07:45.733 --> 07:48.268
Peace be with you.

07:48.335 --> 07:52.906
Uh, we were told, uh,
Millie Banks was here.
I-- I guess she's a nun.

07:52.973 --> 07:57.578
Millie's not just a nun.
No, no. She's special.

07:57.645 --> 07:59.813
She's his favorite.

07:59.880 --> 08:03.684
We're all brides of God,
Sister Kate.
He loves all of us.

08:03.751 --> 08:07.454
But he only speaks
to some of us.

08:07.521 --> 08:11.692
Sister Millie heard
the direct voice of God...
12 times.

08:11.759 --> 08:13.927
Three decades I've been here.

08:13.994 --> 08:16.964
All I ever got
was a heat rash
shaped like Palestine.

08:20.400 --> 08:23.637
[ Earl Narrating ] It was a
reflective area, and we weren't
allowed to talk to each other.

08:23.704 --> 08:26.073
So Randy couldn't tell me
when he got distracted...

08:26.139 --> 08:28.976
by the most beautiful room
he'd ever seen.

08:31.244 --> 08:35.583
We later learned
those were prayer candles
and not birthday-wish candles.

08:35.649 --> 08:39.687
Luckily, before blowin' 'em out,
he wished for everyone's
prayers to come true.

08:42.422 --> 08:46.526
There she is--
the Lord whisperer.

08:46.594 --> 08:50.063
* Frère Jacques
Frère Jacques *

08:50.130 --> 08:53.000
[ Bell Tolling ]
* Dormez-vous
Dormez-vous *

08:53.066 --> 08:58.305
* La-la-la-la-tina
La-la-la-la-tina *

08:58.371 --> 09:00.373
* Ding, dang, dong *

09:00.440 --> 09:03.944
* Ding, dang, dong **

09:04.011 --> 09:06.379
N-Nun Millie?
[ Bell Tolling Ends ]

09:06.446 --> 09:10.818
Oh, my goodness.
I remember you.

09:10.884 --> 09:15.388
What a neat surprise!
How is that cuddly
brother of yours?

09:15.455 --> 09:18.425
And that adorable bride?

09:18.491 --> 09:21.762
I know.
I'm nice now.

09:21.829 --> 09:24.598
Weird, huh?
[ Chuckles ]

09:24.665 --> 09:26.967
[ Earl Narrating ]
I explained to Millie about
Joy's restrainin' order,

09:27.034 --> 09:29.837
and she was
happy to help out.

09:32.405 --> 09:34.241
There you go.

09:34.307 --> 09:37.010
I was a real turd
in the hot tub back then,

09:37.077 --> 09:40.413
but now I throw
birthday parties for orphans.

09:40.480 --> 09:42.983
It's great, 'cause their parents
really haven't spoiled 'em.

09:43.050 --> 09:46.453
'Cause they don't have any.
That's touching.

09:46.519 --> 09:48.722
I make all
the cakes myself.

09:48.789 --> 09:51.391
That's how I met
little Celeste here.

09:51.458 --> 09:53.426
I used to live
in a storm drain.

09:53.493 --> 09:55.495
Rain washed
my doll heads away.

09:55.562 --> 09:59.366
That sounds horrible.
I once lived in my car
for two months.

09:59.432 --> 10:03.070
Did you ever have to move
'cause a pack of stray dogs
kicked you out of your house?

10:06.940 --> 10:09.743
Let's not
make this a contest.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.912
Well, I'm glad
I could help Joy.

10:11.979 --> 10:14.314
You could bring her
some cake if you want to.

10:14.381 --> 10:18.418
Well, actually, uh,
I'm not here just for Joy.

10:18.485 --> 10:20.387
I-I'm here because,

10:20.453 --> 10:23.857
see, I got this list
of all the bad things
I've done to people,

10:23.924 --> 10:26.827
and, you see,
that voice of God
you were hearin'--

10:28.061 --> 10:30.130
that was--

10:30.197 --> 10:32.099
well, that was me.

10:32.165 --> 10:34.601
Yeah, right.

10:34.668 --> 10:37.170
Did Sister Kate
put you up to this?

10:37.237 --> 10:40.841
I mean, the fact that
the Lord talked to me
really gets her habit in a wad.

10:43.476 --> 10:45.612
[ Sighs ]

10:45.679 --> 10:49.282
"Waxeth" thy neighbor's
El Camino.

10:49.349 --> 10:51.885
Oh, my goodness.

10:51.952 --> 10:55.255
"Showeth" thy hindquarters
to the mailman.

10:55.322 --> 10:58.491
Yeah, I get it.
I get it. It was you.

10:58.558 --> 11:02.996
Okay.
That's good to know.

11:04.264 --> 11:06.633
It was a nice trick.

11:06.700 --> 11:09.402
I suppose I had it comin'.

11:10.570 --> 11:14.307
Man, you really got me.

11:14.374 --> 11:19.046
You made me start a whole new
life based on lies.

11:19.112 --> 11:22.182
Filthy, stinking,
rotten lies!

11:24.084 --> 11:25.986
You threw out
my birthday cake!

11:26.053 --> 11:29.022
Oh, like you've never eaten
out of a trash can before!

11:31.358 --> 11:35.763
- [ Paper Tearing ]
- Is there anyone on your list
who wants a daughter?

11:35.829 --> 11:38.698
I don't know.
Hold on.

11:41.334 --> 11:43.503
Yeah, right here.

11:43.570 --> 11:47.307
Oh, wait.
Uh, he wants a son.

11:56.116 --> 11:58.051
Yeah.

12:03.123 --> 12:05.192
[ Earl Narrating ]
I thought tellin' Millie
the truth...

12:05.258 --> 12:08.161
about pretendin'
to be the voice of God
would be a good thing.

12:08.228 --> 12:10.463
But instead of
makin' things better,

12:10.530 --> 12:12.332
well, it made things
a lot worse.

12:12.399 --> 12:15.468
She left the convent and moved
back to the trailer park.

12:15.535 --> 12:17.504
And she was
angrier than ever.

12:17.570 --> 12:21.708
She kicked up more trouble
than that tornado
that took everyone's pets.

12:21.775 --> 12:23.777
She stopped watchin'
her preacher shows,

12:23.844 --> 12:27.214
washin' her hair
and waterin' her plants.

12:34.554 --> 12:38.158
She didn't even enjoy her
daily grilled cheese anymore.

12:38.225 --> 12:40.227
And she seemed
even angrier at squirrels.

12:40.293 --> 12:42.162
Die!

12:42.229 --> 12:44.231
[ Slingshot Fires ]
[ Squirrel Chitters ]

12:44.297 --> 12:47.434
It's wild.
You doing right actually
did this lady wrong.

12:47.500 --> 12:49.369
That's what I was thinkin'.

12:49.436 --> 12:52.639
- Only not worded clever
like that.
- Way to go, dummy.

12:52.705 --> 12:56.143
Not only is Millie not cancelin'
my restrainin' order, but now
she broke Darnell's heart.

12:56.209 --> 12:59.847
Tell him, Darnell.
Yeah, she--

12:59.913 --> 13:02.349
She, um-- She-- She--

13:02.415 --> 13:05.152
- She evicted Mr. Turtle.
- [ Gasps ]
From his shell?

13:07.921 --> 13:09.789
Well, that's where he lives.

13:09.857 --> 13:12.325
[ Earl Narrating ]
Millie was an equal
opportunity harasser.

13:12.392 --> 13:14.527
She picked on all races,
creeds and species.

13:14.594 --> 13:16.830
Hey, shrub head.

13:16.897 --> 13:18.999
That your turtle?

13:19.066 --> 13:22.235
No one owns Mr. Turtle,
but he is my friend.

13:22.302 --> 13:25.105
Well, your friend's gonna
have to be gone by tomorrow.

13:25.172 --> 13:27.640
There's no reptiles allowed
in the trailer park.

13:27.707 --> 13:29.576
Unless you wanna
make soup.

13:36.283 --> 13:38.151
Joy!

13:40.353 --> 13:43.123
Yeah, now I gotta find
the little guy a foster home.

13:43.190 --> 13:45.926
Earl. Earl. Earl. Earl.

13:45.993 --> 13:48.761
Earl. Earl.
Yeah, we can be
foster parents.

13:48.828 --> 13:50.830
Yes!
I love turtles.

13:50.898 --> 13:54.301
I love turtles too.
Especially you.

13:54.367 --> 13:57.938
God, why do men
wait so long to tell
their turtles how they feel?

13:58.005 --> 14:01.174
They need to say those
simple words-- "I love you."

14:04.878 --> 14:07.414
This sucks
the big one, Earl.

14:07.480 --> 14:10.083
I know. I'm sorry, guys.
I feel awful about this.

14:10.150 --> 14:12.185
The list is
supposed to help people,

14:12.252 --> 14:15.422
not screw everything up
and kick turtles out of
their home.

14:15.488 --> 14:17.925
Don't worry, Darnell.
You can come over
whenever you want.

14:17.991 --> 14:19.859
But give it a couple weeks.

14:19.927 --> 14:22.996
We don't wanna make this
more confusing for him
than it already is.

14:23.063 --> 14:25.565
You should
make her go back.

14:27.067 --> 14:29.069
If everyone was happy
when that lady was a nun,

14:29.136 --> 14:31.071
you have to make
her go back.

14:31.138 --> 14:34.874
Give her a sign or something,
like a burning sheep walking
through the middle of town.

14:34.942 --> 14:36.743
That's what made my brother
be a priest.

14:36.809 --> 14:40.080
At the risk of
agreeing with the maid,
she's got a point.

14:40.147 --> 14:43.250
- I say we torch a sheep.
- We're not torchin' a sheep.

14:43.316 --> 14:45.852
But the whole sign thing
isn't a bad idea.

14:45.919 --> 14:49.189
We made her a nun
the first time.
Maybe we can do it again.

14:49.256 --> 14:51.758
We're gonna have
so much fun together,
Mr. Turtle.

14:51.824 --> 14:55.128
Can I call you
by your first name?
He doesn't have one.

14:55.195 --> 14:57.897
Then I'll give you one.
Randy.

14:57.965 --> 15:02.002
[ Earl Narrating ] We needed
to find a sign to put Millie
back on the righteous path,

15:02.069 --> 15:03.971
so we stole Bibles
from the motel.

15:04.037 --> 15:08.008
I'm tellin' you,
we drive her down to SeaWorld
and get a whale to swallow her.

15:08.075 --> 15:11.611
- That'd be a sign.
- Those are Shamu whales.
They'd chew her up first.

15:11.678 --> 15:15.015
Fine. What if we went down
to SeaWorld and got the penguins
to do a nativity scene?

15:15.082 --> 15:17.217
Randy, we're not
goin' to SeaWorld.

15:17.284 --> 15:19.419
I think we should go back
to my locust idea.

15:19.486 --> 15:22.755
I don't know.
Locusts are tricky.
You can't reason with 'em.

15:22.822 --> 15:25.525
Got it!
Right here.

15:28.061 --> 15:31.131
[ Earl Narrating ]
We thought turnin' water
into wine might be cool.

15:31.198 --> 15:35.268
We hoped Millie would be
as impressed as the people
in ancient Jesus time.

15:37.370 --> 15:39.906
Unfortunately, a birdbath full
of wine in a trailer park...

15:39.973 --> 15:42.675
will last about as long as,

15:42.742 --> 15:46.013
well, a birdbath full of wine
in a trailer park.
[ Snoring ]

15:46.079 --> 15:50.617
We found this incredible miracle
in the Bible that Randy was
really excited about tryin'.

15:50.683 --> 15:54.421
Apparently, some guy named
Balaam had a talkin' ass.

15:54.487 --> 15:56.756
Randy couldn't wait
to show Millie his.

15:56.823 --> 15:59.326
Earl, wait!
Wait!

15:59.392 --> 16:01.394
I just read
the whole thing.

16:01.461 --> 16:05.765
The ass was Balaam's donkey.
It was a talkin' donkey.

16:05.832 --> 16:08.301
Randy, plan's off!
Abort!

16:08.368 --> 16:11.438
[ Earl Narrating ]
I started to realize
miracles are really hard.

16:11.504 --> 16:15.308
I guess that's why
they're usually just done
by God and TV magicians.

16:17.810 --> 16:20.413
Then I had the answer.

16:22.015 --> 16:23.916
Don't make the beard
too long.

16:23.983 --> 16:26.753
I know how to burn a Jesus face
in a grilled cheese, Earl.

16:26.819 --> 16:29.322
Suit yourself.
He's just lookin'
a little ZZ Top is all.

16:29.389 --> 16:31.258
Fine.

16:32.292 --> 16:34.761
I think it looks
like Abe Lincoln.

16:34.827 --> 16:38.098
If only we had a
Stephen Douglas grilled cheese,
we could make them debate.

16:38.165 --> 16:40.200
Yeah. I don't
know who that is,

16:40.267 --> 16:42.369
but I love the idea
of grilled cheese arguin'.

16:43.770 --> 16:46.073
[ Earl Narrating ]
After three hours
of fryin' cheese,

16:46.139 --> 16:48.375
we finally got
our magic sandwich.

16:48.441 --> 16:50.343
Then we had to lure Millie
away from hers.

16:50.410 --> 16:52.612
** [ Heavy Metal On Stereo ]

16:55.082 --> 16:57.850
Bass notes.

16:57.917 --> 16:59.752
** [ Continues ]

17:01.521 --> 17:04.357
[ Earl Narrating ]
I never saw a real miracle,

17:04.424 --> 17:07.527
but I did see those movies
where George Burns was God.

17:07.594 --> 17:10.230
I knew that our sandwich
needed a little extra something.

17:17.670 --> 17:21.308
- Whoa! What the--
- What are you doin' in my house
messin' with my stuff?

17:21.374 --> 17:24.777
No, no. Look-- Look--
Look, Millie. I-- I was outside,
and I heard this angel sound.

17:24.844 --> 17:26.846
You know.
** [ High Note ]

17:26.913 --> 17:28.948
And I was drawn to it,
and behold--

17:29.015 --> 17:31.751
Holy!
No, Millie, look, hold on!

17:31.818 --> 17:33.786
It's a miracle Lord sandwich!

17:34.921 --> 17:38.625
Ow! Man, that is
not necessary!

17:38.691 --> 17:40.793
Hey, Earl, I think
Millie's comin' back.

17:42.195 --> 17:45.398
I'm too young!
[ Grunts ]

17:49.202 --> 17:51.171
You saved me,
Mr. Turtle.

17:51.238 --> 17:53.706
If it wasn't for you,
I'd have been shot.

17:55.208 --> 17:57.344
[ Grunts ]

17:59.846 --> 18:04.217
Would you just stop it!
Stop bein' such a miserable,
crazy bitch!

18:04.284 --> 18:06.253
I'm sorry for usin'
the "B" word, ma'am,

18:06.319 --> 18:08.688
but that's what you are,
except at the convent.

18:08.755 --> 18:11.924
There, you were sweet
and made cakes for mopey kids.

18:11.991 --> 18:15.662
Because of a lie.
So, who cares
how you got there?

18:15.728 --> 18:18.865
You were nice.
You weren't shootin' people
in the earlobe and the forehead.

18:18.931 --> 18:21.834
[ Randy Groaning ]

18:23.069 --> 18:25.104
Run and get help,
Mr. Turtle.

18:27.640 --> 18:29.942
Faster.

18:30.009 --> 18:33.513
Look, all we were doin'
was tryin' to make you
a happy nun again...

18:33.580 --> 18:35.648
by sneakin' you a sandwich
with Jesus on it.

18:35.715 --> 18:38.151
- That's crazy.
- You wanna know what's crazy?

18:38.218 --> 18:40.019
People waitin' for some
big sign to push them...

18:40.086 --> 18:42.322
into doin' somethin'
they oughta be doin'
in the first place.

18:42.389 --> 18:46.693
It's like me.
I'd still be a low-life dirtbag
if I wasn't hit by a car.

18:46.759 --> 18:49.762
And you were a miserable
"B" word until you heard
the voice of God.

18:49.829 --> 18:53.833
What were we waitin' for?
We could've been better people
all on our own.

18:53.900 --> 18:55.468
But whatever.

18:55.535 --> 18:59.739
If you wanna wait for
a magic sign to go be happy,
then good luck to you, lady.

18:59.806 --> 19:02.509
I'm walkin' out now to go help
my possibly dyin' brother.

19:02.575 --> 19:05.745
You can shoot me
in the back of the head
if you want to.

19:05.812 --> 19:08.381
You're my sign.

19:08.448 --> 19:12.319
- What?
- You're my sign from above.

19:12.385 --> 19:15.688
I was a lot happier at that
convent, bakin' and stuff.

19:15.755 --> 19:19.559
You were sent to put me
back on my path.

19:19.626 --> 19:22.829
Wow.
Weird.

19:22.895 --> 19:25.498
I guess angels
don't have to be beautiful.

19:27.267 --> 19:29.936
Well, my whole point
was that you shouldn't
really need a sign,

19:30.002 --> 19:33.840
but if me bein' a messenger
from God works for you,
I'm cool with it.

19:33.906 --> 19:36.243
[ Randy Groans ]

19:36.309 --> 19:39.546
When you go to nun school,
do they give you any
first aid training?

19:39.612 --> 19:41.781
Like how to treat
a head wound?

19:44.851 --> 19:46.886
[ Earl Narrating ]
Apparently, they do.

19:48.087 --> 19:51.190
- ** [ Women Vocalizing ]
- [ Both Laugh ]

19:53.293 --> 19:57.730
* When you see
the Southern Cross
for the first time *

19:57.797 --> 19:59.732
[ Earl Narrating ]
And like I always say,

19:59.799 --> 20:02.369
when you do good things,
good things happen--

20:02.435 --> 20:05.638
like restraining orders
bein' lifted.

20:05.705 --> 20:08.308
* 'Cause the truth you might
be runnin' from is so small *

20:08.375 --> 20:10.209
[ Earl Narrating ]
And turtles comin' home.

20:10.277 --> 20:13.580
- * But it's as big
as the promise *
- I love you, Mr. Turtle.

20:13.646 --> 20:18.050
* The promise of
a comin' day *
[ Clears Throat ]

20:18.117 --> 20:21.220
* So I'm sailin' for tomorrow *

20:21.288 --> 20:24.023
* My dreams are a-dyin' *

20:24.090 --> 20:25.992
* And we never failed-- *

20:26.058 --> 20:30.430
[ Earl Narrating ]
And orphan girls reunitin'
with their cake-bakin' friends.

20:30.497 --> 20:33.065
And scary-lookin' dolls
gettin' back their little heads.

20:33.132 --> 20:35.568
* Survive being bested *

20:35.635 --> 20:37.670
* Somebody fine-- **

20:37.737 --> 20:39.639
[ Earl Narrating ]
And even though Millie
needed a sign...

20:39.706 --> 20:41.908
to do what she knew
in her heart was right,

20:41.974 --> 20:46.879
I wasn't gonna wait any longer
to do somethin' I should've
done a long time ago.

20:46.946 --> 20:49.282
I love you, Randy.

20:49.349 --> 20:51.451
I love you too, Earl.

20:54.287 --> 20:57.690
I gotta go take a leak.
I'm gonna go
play with the radio.
